---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro'

// Plain-language privacy policy. Reasonable starter for an
// Australian SaaS using Supabase (Sydney region) for storage and
// Stripe for payments. Before going live for real money, get a
// lawyer to review — Australian Privacy Principles compliance is
// straightforward but the GDPR / overseas-user angle deserves
// professional language if you sell internationally.
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Privacy Policy — Beme"
  description="What data Beme collects, why, and what you can do about it."
>
  <article class="container-tight max-w-3xl mx-auto" style="padding-top: clamp(5rem, 7vw, 9rem); padding-bottom: clamp(4rem, 6vw, 6rem);">
    <div class="text-xs uppercase tracking-wider text-beme-400 font-semibold mb-4">
      Legal
    </div>
    <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold text-ink-50 tracking-tight">
      Privacy Policy
    </h1>
    <p class="text-sm text-ink-400 mt-3">
      Last updated: June 2026
    </p>

    <div class="mt-10 space-y-10 text-[16px] text-ink-200 leading-relaxed">
      <section>
        <p>
          Short version: we collect what we need to run Beme and
          nothing more. We don't sell your data, we don't share it
          with advertisers, and you can see, export, or delete it
          whenever you want.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-ink-50 mb-3">What we collect</h2>
        <p>
          <strong class="text-ink-50">Account info.</strong> Your
          email address, name, and (if you sign in with Microsoft)
          the basic profile details Microsoft passes back.
        </p>
        <p class="mt-3">
          <strong class="text-ink-50">Project data.</strong> Everything
          you build inside Beme — projects, wall types, supply rates,
          PDF references. We store it so the software works and so
          your work is there when you log back in.
        </p>
        <p class="mt-3">
          <strong class="text-ink-50">Usage data.</strong> Basic
          information about how you use the app (pages visited,
          features used, browser type) so we can fix bugs and improve
          the product. We don't track you across the web.
        </p>
        <p class="mt-3">
          <strong class="text-ink-50">Payment info.</strong> If you
          subscribe, payment details are handled by Stripe — we
          never see your card number. We only see whether your
          subscription is active and the email you paid with.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-ink-50 mb-3">Where it's stored</h2>
        <p>
          Project and account data are stored in Supabase's Sydney
          region. Payment data is handled by Stripe. Both providers
          use industry-standard encryption in transit and at rest.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-ink-50 mb-3">Who sees it</h2>
        <p>
          Only the team that runs Beme, and only when needed (e.g.
          if you ask for support and we need to look at your account
          to help). We don't sell your data, share it with
          advertisers, or use it for anything beyond running the
          service.
        </p>
        <p class="mt-3">
          If you're on a Team or Enterprise plan, other users on your
          team can see the shared library and team-level projects
          per the role you've assigned them.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-ink-50 mb-3">Your rights</h2>
        <p>
          You can access, export, correct, or delete your data at
          any time from your account settings. If you'd prefer we
          handle a request directly, email
          <a href="mailto:hello@beme.com.au" class="text-beme-400 hover:text-beme-300 underline">
            hello@beme.com.au
          </a>
          and we'll act within a reasonable timeframe.
        </p>
        <p class="mt-3">
          If you cancel your subscription, your data stays
          accessible for 30 days so you can export. After that it
          may be deleted from active storage. Backups roll over on
          a longer schedule.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-ink-50 mb-3">Cookies</h2>
        <p>
          We use cookies (and similar local storage) for two things:
          keeping you logged in, and remembering your preferences
          (theme, last-opened project). We don't use third-party
          tracking cookies.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-ink-50 mb-3">Updates</h2>
        <p>
          If we update this policy in a meaningful way, we'll let
          active users know by email. The "Last updated" date at the
          top of this page is always current.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-ink-50 mb-3">Contact</h2>
        <p>
          Questions or requests:
          <a href="mailto:hello@beme.com.au" class="text-beme-400 hover:text-beme-300 underline">
            hello@beme.com.au
          </a>.
        </p>
      </section>
    </div>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
